Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%carton} in a #sieve{}, then pat dry with
#kitchen paper{}.

Spread the chickpeas onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, sprinkle
over the @Roasted Spice and Herb Blend{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Roast on the middle shelf of your #oven{} until crispy, ~{16-18%minutes}.
Carefully remove from the oven and turn halfway through.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to
the boil.

When the pan of water is boiling, add the @orzo{180%grams} and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{10%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a sieve and run under cold water. Drizzle with
@olive oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the chickpeas roast, zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @pesto{64%grams}, lemon juice,
@olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp} and a pinch of salt and pepper. Set your
dressing aside.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%grams}.

Stir the tomatoes through the dressing and set aside to macerate.

When the chickpeas have 5 mins remaining, remove the tray from the oven.
Drizzle over the @honey{1%tbsp}, toss to coat, then return to the oven for the
remaining time.

When everything's ready, add the cooked orzo, @wild rocket{40%grams} and half
the chickpeas to the dressing bowl. Mix to combine.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Share your orzo salad between your serving bowls.

Top with the remaining chickpeas and crumble over the
@Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%grams}.

Sprinkle over a pinch of lemon zest to finish.

Enjoy!